cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CR 

This paper is about improving the quality of cardinality estimation, which is a core problem in query optimization in databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper proposes a new deep learning approach to cardinality estimation, which involves training a multi-set convolutional network to capture query features and true cardinalities. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper addresses weaknesses in sampling-based estimation, which could make it relevant to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
